author: @ms.d88
text: Now I understand why Hoshi chose Getting Closer as the song with a harder choreo when the Performance Unit was asked which song had a more difficult choreography (choosing between HIT and Getting Closer). Focus on him. Even from the start, he already has the most difficult position and then he travels from left to right then front to back. And have you noticed how he has that position from 0:33 then suddenly stands up and moves to his right and then center to do his part of the song (exactly from 0:33-0:38)? That takes a lot of energy and focus. Look at how he travels backwards from in front to the back at 2:09 to 2:13. That's amazing especially if you have a lot of members in a group. You need to be mindful of the formation while moving. He is indeed the Performance Unit leader and the main dancer. Also, I appreciate how DINO was giving his all in this choreography video. They were all giving their 100% but Dino caught my attention too. He was giving his 200% here. Kudos Seventeen!!!!

author: @deodate2995
text: i know fuckall about choreographing and haven't taken dance since i was 12 but to add two cents as someone who's been doing art my whole life: visual composition is tough to perfect on a still image, so i can't fathom the amount of consideration it takes for a continually moving picture made up of THIRTEEN individual-minded parts. they make fantastic use of stillness and motion and speed and placement to direct the eye where it's supposed to go without ever becoming visually unclear in the more transitional parts of the dance. i don't think we compliment for their synchronization too much because adding that on to the artistry and physical energy it takes to make something like this is fucking insane. seventeen are so so good at what they do.

author: @Sebisajiminstan
text:
This remains one of my favorite choreos ever. From them or anyone else. It is so pleasing to the eye, they are so perfectly in sync with each other and the beat, and the formations and transitions are INSANE. There is absolutely no one who can challenge Seventeen in terms of choreography, period.
It’s not just cause they have a lot of members either, it’s cause they know how to use that to create something spectacular. Like, I was looking at NCT’s performances, and they have almost double the people on stage, but their performances are always lacking and disconnected. They do not use the potential of having 20+ people at all. 
Look at SVT’s formations, at any point during this song. They are always interesting to look at, and they manage to keep the transitions flawless as well. There’s no awkwardly standing by in position, waiting for the beat, there’s no pause, the member leaving center stage is already in the middle of a move, as is the member now taking the center. And everyone else is always moving. And the freaking levels? During this whole performance? Mindblowing. Especially Woozi’s verse, Hoshi’s chorus part and Wonwoo’s at the end. 
I could talk about this choreo for hours, it’s so well made and executed. Brilliant.

author: @karitthasun290
text:
As I'm watching this dance practice, I'm amazed how I can remember all 13 members, given how I'm a month-old Carat. 

I used to think that my memory isn't good and was scared that I could never succeed in med school with its heavy memorization. But now, becoming a Carat gave me so much confidence. Seventeen is one of the biggest groups in kpop. From not being able to tell Jeonghan and Joshua apart, I can bravely say I can distinguish them in the dark by just their cough. Not only do I remember how many siblings each of them have, but I also remember their full name lineup forward and backward, GoSe iconic lines, the location of their beauty marks, their food allergy, their habits, and quirks, and other 100+ TMI they said before. Memorizing a thousand body parts and functions would not be any more difficult than memorizing facts about Seventeen x 7-years-worth of information about them x their lifespan info so far. 

Being a carat really boosted my confidence a lot. I'm ready for med school!

author: @rin_box
text:
I love Seventeen, I really do... but since we're stuck in quarantine, I keep on wishing they'd release more lives of the b-sides... We're spoiled already, I know, 2 comebacks in Japan and Korea in 2020, and the masterpiece that is An Ode last year... but I can't understand why songs like Network Love, Lie Again, I Wish, and Kidult haven't been performed live yet. The titles this year,  Left & Right and Homerun are amazing we need positivity to survive this pandemic... Still, I wish they'd also perform all the age-line songs and All My Love (which has the same dramatic lyrics as DWC). Personally though, my all-time fave Semicolon song is Light A Flame, and right after they have a 96line perf, can they please perform it as OT13??  

... which is why I'm looking forward to the year-end shows... I don't care about the awards (I'm still voting, ofc!), all the hype & glory could go to BTS and Blackpink, I'll shrug it off... BUT the Korean public, and the rest of the Kpop world, are missing out on Seventeen's amazing lives. I don't even mean risky formations or exhausting choreography. They're already acknowledged as the best & most synchronized dance group in South Korea. I wish for lives when they'd just sit, sing/rap, and let the songs and their voices + visuals  shine through.

author: @8BCA84
text:
lemme just point a few things:

1) the formations and transitions are amazing. it’s already hard enough to place certain arrangements w many members (trust me, the struggle is real. i rmb drawing too many circles just for the formation itself and had too many corrections for the transition) but this is what makes svt really unique. they made use of their number and made it as their strength. 

2) i could roughly imagine the amount of practice that was poured into this choreography like any of their songs. to be that synchronized, they must have done this a lot. every move ingrained in their muscle memory.

3) in a kpop, it’s difficult to form a group with similar style of dancing but svt is once again, different. the feel for each member connects w another member that connects to another and that makes this team solid asf. almost like they audition for the same troop w the same genre. that’s the reason why you struggle to find the main dancer or perf. team or can’t focus on one person because you have to look at the piece as a whole to appreciate it more. 

4) lastly, it’s not much noticeable but i like the fact they adjust accordingly to their position whenever they feel like they’re out of the formation. One example of this would be Hoshi adjusting to S. Coups kick in 1:28 because as SC cannot exactly look back to check if he’s going to hit HS, the other must condition himself to avoid accidents as such. another would be Dino stepping back in 2:30. one trait of being a good dancer in a group is becoming aware of his members, conscious or not. 

i can’t believe i typed this long but truly, svt is one hardworking unit. they deserve every award there is. i am saying this as someone who has an experience in dancing so pls excuse me if i over analyze a detail or two.

author: @ohyesmmmhmisssharon2358
text:
You can't really expect less from this group. The best in dancing! And so flawless much smoother than your face!(jk lol)

I've never really seen anyone do this so might as well do it:

Why they're the best? Cuz they make the cleanest dance. Which is very difficult to achieve btw if you're dancing in a group this big. How do you think they made it clean? Through proper execution. Like if you gotta bend your knees 90 degrees you gotta do it at 90. No more no less. That's the very basic principle in dancing to avoid clutter especially if you're dancing in a group. As dancer myself, the actions their doing are actually simple if you slowed it down. What made it difficult tho is cuz of the tempo. It's fast and if you're a dancer of only one genre then this is gonna be real difficult to you (when I transitioned from contemporary to pop I was having massive difficulty cuz of the difference but luckily I was able to get it down quicker than contemporary). Again what made it beautiful tho despite the simplicity is the execution. They did it PERFECTLY. Now in the dancing world there's a saying, "Simple and clean is ALWAYS better." Cuz it's hard to nail clean in difficult actions such as acrobats incorporated in the dance. If you've watched a lot of choreography and if you're a dancer you'll understand what I meant.

Now to those who wanted to cover this and already covered this but meh: 
Take note you gotta execute this properly. You gotta bend, reach, kneel, bounce and jump according to the choreography. DO NOT overdo it or you'll destroy the dance and practice countless times to nail down the beat. You'll notice big change in your dancing if you do this two. Looking cool and sexy is the least of your concern. You'll look much cooler and sexier if you dance properly. Remember that execution is everything to emphasize the dance, creativity always comes second.

And please spare me the lesson about you dancing this in your own style. Being lazy in following proper execution is not a "style", you're just lazy. Notice how a lot of people do the same dance but in their own style. Did they slack off? Nooooo they still execute it properly and beautifully. They just added a few flicks and twists of here and there to make it their own.

author: @히수-u2u
text:
플디... 진짜 이게뭐에요..올릴거면 셉틴채널에 다 올려주세요... 그렇다고 이영상을 플디채널에 올리란건 아니지만 ㅎ님들이 무슨짓을 하든 우리 캐럿은 뜻 절대 안굽히고 계정통합 결사반대 할거니까 각오하시는게 좋을거같네옹^!^ 그전에 만행도 많았고, 한층, 아니 몇층 더 잘생기고 실력도 늘고 멋있어지구 귀엽고 완벽해져서 온 우리 세봉이들한테 제발....플디보다 유명해서 질투라도 하시는거에요..?이봐요 님들 소속사에요...만행보니까 빡쳐서 쓰는 글인데, 제발 아티스트 보호해주세요 팬들 마음도, 셉틴 입장도 생각해주세요 초딩한테도 이렇게 욕먹으시는데 진짜 안 부끄러우시나요?일도 안하신다고 팬들 사이에 완전 빡쳤어요 피드백도 안내주시고 숨고 그냥 님들 생각만 하고 소속사가 가수를 더 키워줄 생각을 해야지 오히려 뜨려는 애들 발목을 잡으면 어떡합니까? 말로만 소속사지 그냥 돈먹는 귀신인가요? 님들이 한 짓에 대한 피드백 내놓으세요.
그리고 처음부터 다시 설명하는것 같지만 우리는 플디의 팬이 아니고 세븐틴의 팬입니다 우리가 굳이 내가수를 내손으로 티저 영상과 뮤비 영상에 싫어요를 누르고, 신고를 해야겠나요? 저도 진짜 이러기 싫은데 그걸 플디가 받쳐줬으면 합니다; 님들의 그 몇마디 때문에 실트 1위는 가뿐하고요 캐럿은 진심 빡쳤는데 보고 어떤 기분이 드는지 대충 이해가 가네요 ㅋ 숨이차도 세븐틴의 소중한 노랜데 음원하나 안내고 티저랑 뮤비, 안무영상만 달랑 내놓고 그냥 튀는건가요..? 전에 준휘 솔로곡 광고?도 안했다구 들었는뎅 ㅋㅋㅋ플레디스 더의상 시간 역행하지 마시고 현실로 돌아오세요.애타는 캐럿 심정 이해해주시고 더이상 못기다려요 한번 더 말하지만 피드백 내놓으세요
자 다음으로 숨이차 완전 짱임❤❤❤❤ 노래는 완전 좋고 귀엽고 상큼발랄한 어쩌나하고 다르게 멋있어서 색다른 눈호강 귀호강 했답니다ㅠ 제가 입덕한지 얼마안되서 정한이 머리긴것도 얼마전에 봤더니 너무 잘어울리는거 보고 한번반하고 금발보고 오늘 또 두번반함..(코피쥬륵)❗💟💟 우리원우 파마도 개멋있고♡승관이 흑발->파란색으로 염색했던데 뿌루베리..넘 귀여워서 또반함..ㅜㅅㅜ ((원우 인이어좀 사주세요오 )) 그나저나 21일 컴백 기대합니당 ❤ 마지막으로 우리 셉틴 언제나 흥했으면 좋겠고, 곁에 항상 캐럿이 있으니 플디가 어떤짓을 해도 호이ㅣ팅!!(이쯤되면 김민규 오타지만 명언 ㅎㅎㅎ귀여워) 힘내!!ㅠㅠㅠㅠ 그럴일 없어야겠지만...(플디 반성하세요) 꽃길만 걷자 세븐틴!!!!!!♡❤💓💕💖💘💗💙💚💛🧡💜💝💞💟❣💌 사랑해!!

author: @Syndromed99
text:
One of my favourite things about SVT as a group is the way they so skillfully utilise their numbers in the choreographing aspect of their songs.
Because SVT has more members than the average Kpop group (which has, on average, around 7 members -- that's nearly HALF of what SVT has) choreos can quickly become crowded or start to look messy if they're not handled well. However, SVT has consistently resisted that issue and shown choreos that are beautiful and intricate BECAUSE of the large numbers instead of DESPITE the large number of members. 

For example, around 1:38 when the members are lined up and do this slow motion, sort of...unfolding(?) move with their arms and bodies -- I replayed that part multiple times because it was so strangely entrancing. The reason a move like that works so well is because they have so many members, but the large amount of members also make moves like that difficult, because if even one of them is a little off on their timing, it messes up the flow and aesthetic of the move completely.  And yet, they pull it off beautifully AND they quickly transition from that slower move to a faster more powerful one in the span of like 1 second, which is hard as hell to do in small numbers, let alone with THIRTEEN people.

So what I'm saying is: STAN TALENT, STAN SEVENTEEN.

(this was a hella long post of me pretty much just being pretentious and gushing about these 13 incredible boys who I adore with all my heart and soul)

author: @chwenotchew7409
text:
at first i thought Vernon is Dino😂
because Dino wear that Balenciaga shirt at Flower MV

This videos, this song for me is the translation of so much hard work, team work, patience, confidence, courage, potential, talent, believe, love, blood, tear, sweat. After so many incredible songs, concepts and choreographys that had us amazed, and with higher and higher expectations, Seventeen come, just when the year is about to end and we all didn't expected nothing more, and give us this woderful piece of work.  Gosh!! verything here is so soooooo impressive, spetacular that I have to give all the congratualations to this incredible team, my 13 boys that i love and cherish and admire so dearly, who never fail to make me laugh, smile, feel that i'm part of this family, that i'm special and friends with each one of them just for being a carat. But mostly Seventeen never fails in show to the world the results of giving them a chance, QUALITY WORK, QUALITY MUSIC, TRULY ARTIST. Kind and inocent hearts, but also brave. 

Thank you so much, my 13 diamonds, for show me that hard work paids off, tallent always needs to be molded, together we get more, we are better than alone, and to believe in my dreams, that starts hard, from the bottom, but live your life doing what you love makes all the difference. 

I'm sorry the loong comment. I just love this boys so much and needed to tell somehow.

text: honestly, this is not my favorite SVT song, but that's jst because I'm not really into hiphop.  But the choreo keeps me watching over and over again.  It's just so intricate and so sync, it keeps you intrigued for days.  I love all the formations, and how it highlights everyone.  I've seen sideview pov of this dance, and even then its still interesting.  SVT definitely knows how to use their large group to their advantage in choreography.  I love the layers and symmetry.  I can go on, and I'm not even a dancer or even have a dance background at all, and i'm like waxing poetic about it, it's that good.

Theory time: I know thats Kind of stange but I think there i someone who kills the members. If you look at the teaser of the concerts it looks like a Police/Mafia theme. In one Video it looks like the Vocal unit is the Police that tryes to find out who Killed Seungkwan. They Talk to the Hip hop unit (They are on on table and their Hands are tied to the table with handcuffs). In YMMD Oh My! They are in Heaven but befor that (Prequel from YMMD: Getting Closer) they needed to fear because of the "killer". They now Death is getting closer, the Killer is getting closer. Again it looks like two are the police. This time Dino and Hoshi with their Flashlights. The Clooks could be the time till they all were dead(? Not sure about that). Now the Best part. text: 한성수 사장님 세븐틴의 공을 플레디스의 공으로 돌리지 마세요 세븐틴이 '자체제작돌' 혹은 '가내수공업돌'이란 이유로 책임 지지 않은 일들이 수도 없이 많고 세븐틴에 대한 신뢰가 아닌 플레디스와 한성수 그리고 직원들, 스탭들에 대한 신뢰가 상실됐어요 애들 발목 잡겠답시고 세븐틴이란 그룹명까지도 뺏으셨는데 캐럿들은 그 허울이 아니라 알맹이인 멤버들을 더 소중하게 생각한다는 거 아시죠? 그러니까 허튼 수작 그만 부리세요 존나 같잖고 꼴보기도 싫으니까... 그리고 직원들 교육 똑바로 시키세요 애들도 안 하는 짓을 어른 새끼들이 골빈 것 마냥 ㅋㅋㅋㅋㅋ 잘못된 것에 정당하게 반대를 하는 거고 이의를 제기하는 건데 손가락질에 팬들 기만이요? 지난 시간동안 기만한 걸로도 충분하지 않나요? 플레디스가 이만큼 클 수 있었던 건 소속 아티스트와 그들의 팬들 덕분 아니었나요? 고작 매니저 일이나 하던 사람이 엔터 사업해보겠다고 설쳤을 때 쪽박 안 난 건 다 팬들 덕분입니다 은혜를 뒷통수로 갚는다니 참 안타깝네요 팬들과 실력 있는 아티스트들 아니었음 쫄딱 망해서 빚더미에 짓눌리고 길바닥에 나앉았을 분이 지금 좋은 옷 입고 좋은 거 먹고 좋은 집에서 살고 좋은 것들 누리고 갑질하는 게 다 누구 덕인지 잊으신 모양인데 최대한 빨리 기억이 돌아오시길 바라요 그리고 직원 분들도 똑바로 보세요 님들이 취업률 낮은 대한민국 사회에서 취준생으로 아직까지 안 남아 있는 이유는 근본적으로 팬들 덕분입니다 팬들이 돈 안 썼음 님들은 아직도 취준생으로 그저 그런 사람으로 남아 있을 거라고요 ㅋㅋ 그 일자리 누가 만들어 줬을 것 같아요? 누가 그만큼 회사 키울 수 있게 해 준 것 같아요? 머리 좀만 굴리면 나오는 걸 왜 모르시나 모르겠어요 하기야 대가리가 멍청한데 그 밑에 있는 쫄따구라고 안 멍청하겠어요? 윗물이 썩으면 아랫물도 썩는 거지 ㅋㅋㅋㅋ 한시 바삐 플레디스의 직원들 뇌가 채워지길 바라요~ 사장 새끼나 직원 새끼나 팬들 기만 그만하시고!

author: @sissymayemaye
text:
Hoshi, I...I seriously don't know how you do this. The monster choreo that comes out of this man, it's truly scary. THIS....THIS is what is always brewing in Hoshi's head, people. The man literally eats, sleeps, and breathes dancing 24/7 and barely gets any sleep because THIS is what he's coming up with in his brain. I get exhausted just thinking about what he has to come up with on the daily. Hoshi has to create AND REMEMBER 13 separate choreographies in his head at all times. He has to know what EVERYONE'S steps are, including his own, so he can teach AND monitor the progress of each member. All this while being the happy mood maker of the group, AND dancing so hard to his OWN choreography, that he constantly POPS HIS SHOULDER OUT OF JOINT!! This choreo had me a nervous wreck that his shoulder was going to go out on him again, but there he was, just a poppin and lockin and not even thinking about it. This man is truly amazing (slow claps). By his own admission he can be quick-tempered at times, but can you really blame him? THIS!! THIS SICK, MONSTER, MADDENING AWARD WINNING CHOREO IS IN HIS HEAD ALL THE TIME!! I'm telling you people, Qwon Soon Young is scary.
SCARY !!!!

author: @wilfygloutonny
text: One of the things I like a lot about large groups in k-pop it’s the way they switch the center dancer — and Seventeen it’s one of the best groups to pull that off. I know my opinion may be biased, but really. This guys have a monster coordination and are great dances, not only on solo, but also as a team. They dance as a whole, making one go to the center (usually when they have a their line) and then mixing it with the background as a ‘back-up dancer’. You really can notice that all 13 of them are necessary to make this choreography, and non of their moves are random. Every little detail it’s thought with delicacy. Really, this guys amaze me even more every comeback. Go SVT! 💎

author: @magroves
text:
I am constantly amazed by these 13 young men, their hard work, their dedication, their talent, and their good looks.  

Their dancing is so powerful and synchronized, the music is always interesting and well performed.  Voices like Seungkwans and DK.  Dancing like Jun, Hoshi, Dino and Minghao.  

Woozi is such a good composer.  Hoshi is such a great choreographer and they always fit the songs. I love that so much of the creative process comes right from the group. 

And personalities like DK's sunshine, Hoshi's passion, Seungkwan's friendliness, Woozi's practicality, Vernon's free spirit, Wonwoo's emo side, Mingyu taking care of everyone, Jeonghan being a jokester, and Coup's warm teddy bear side just make me so glad I stan them.

Thus was an amazing performance

It's very well made, and synchronized. They deserved to win best male dance award at MAMAs this year.

author: @AWEsome3GIRl3sam
text: Idk why but when I watch other groups with 10+ members I'd usually think their choreos look overcrowded or messy but with svt everything is so neat and pleasing to the eye. At first I thought it was bc I'm a carat and I just know the members better svts choreos look better but now I see its bc svt always has such even position distribution and smooth formation changes. They dont have every member follow the exact same movements or try to make every member visible which I think makes the choreos look cleaner. Each member has their own specific part that creates a balance which I love. The boys have definitely made their large group  size their advantage when it comes to their choreos 💕💓💕💞💅🏾
